      "description": "A U.S. Fish & Wildlife Service report described widespread wildlife and ecosystem impacts during the “Winter of 77,” including waterfowl die-offs, disease outbreaks, and disrupted migration/distribution patterns. Reported issues included lead poisoning concerns along the Atlantic Flyway, cholera/botulism outbreaks associated with crowding, disrupted salmon and steelhead spawning due to low water in the Pacific Northwest, and winter fish die-offs under ice in parts of the Midwest/Great Lakes region.",
